# Sandbox context — copy into your host `~/.claude/CLAUDE.md`

The sandbox mounts your host `~/.claude/CLAUDE.md` read-only, so the model
sees it every session. Concatenate this block into your own CLAUDE.md so
Claude Code knows it's running inside a sandbox and what the rules are.

---

## You are running inside claude-sandbox

- `--dangerously-skip-permissions` is always passed. The sandbox **is** the
  isolation boundary — prompting for permission on every shell command is not
  the safety model here.
- Working dir: `/workspace` (a per-org named Docker volume; not host-mounted).
- Writable:
  - `/workspace` — per-org; persists across container restarts.
  - `/home/node/.claude/plugins` — host bind-mount (shared with host).
  - `/home/node/.claude/skills` — host bind-mount (shared with host).
  - `/brain` — optional knowledge vault if the user set `BRAIN_PATH` in the
    org's `.env`; otherwise an empty scratch dir.
- Read-only:
  - `/home/node/.claude/settings.json`
  - `/home/node/.claude/CLAUDE.md`
  - `/home/node/.ssh` (so you can `git clone`/`push` via SSH)

## Network

- Firewall is **fail-closed** with an allowlist covering GitHub, npm,
  Anthropic API, Sentry, VS Code marketplace, plus anything set by the org's
  `EXTRA_ALLOWED_DOMAINS`.
- IPv6 is **denied by default**. Outbound traffic is IPv4-only unless
  `IPV6=allow` is set.
- `curl https://example.com` will fail — that's the design. If a legitimate
  host is blocked, ask the user to add it to `EXTRA_ALLOWED_DOMAINS` rather
  than disabling the firewall.
- The allowlist refreshes every 15 min; if a recently-rotated CDN IP is
  briefly unreachable, retrying after 1 min often works.

## Claude CLI wrapper

- `/usr/local/bin/claude` always appends `--dangerously-skip-permissions`.
  You are already running under it.
- The raw binary lives at `/opt/claude-cli/bin/claude` if the wrapper is
  ever in the way.

## Brain vault (optional)

- If `/brain` is mounted with user content, follow the host `CLAUDE.md`
  auto-save rules (decisions, solutions, learnings, daily log).
- If `/brain` is empty (default), skip vault writes silently — no warnings.

## Safe defaults

- Prefer cloning repos under `/workspace/<name>` so they persist across
  container restarts.
- Use SSH (`git@github.com:...`) — the host's `~/.ssh` is mounted read-only.
- When a task seems to need a host-side tool (e.g. VS Code extension, a
  local database), remember the sandbox is isolated; ask the user to run
  it on the host side.
